snippet.textDisplay:
Flight into Terrain by Ed Seaver Vinuesa

If Kobe's leased Sikorsky S-76B helicopter was not equipped with Terrain Awareness and Warning System (TAWS). The National Transportation Safety Board, NTSB, and the The Federal Aviation Administration, FAA, must investigate if the pilot downloaded the TAWS App to his tablet or Smartphone.
Lesson: What lesson can we learn from this tragedy? We can use every tool at our disposal to ensure a safe flight especially when we have family and friends on board.
A safety culture is NOT a checklist item! It's a way of operating that pays attention to details.

The flight was under " Special Visual Flight Rules (Special VFR, SVFR)" If the METAR says 1/2 mile visibility, you will need to file an IFR flight plan or stay at home as a VFR pilot. Once you take off you have to remain clear of clouds and the visibility must be 1 statute miles. An example of the use of SVFR is when a flight wishes to leave an airport in a control zone, to fly VFR in uncontrolled airspace, when the visibility is below the minimum for VFR flight in the control zone but not below the lower minimum for VFR flight in uncontrolled airspace. SVFR is never offered by Air Traffic Control. It must be requested by the Pilot in Command.
"Flight Following" is the provision of an ongoing surveillance information service (SIS) to VFR flights in Class E and G airspace. This service can provide improved situational awareness and assists pilots in avoiding collisions

https://aviation-safety.net/wikibase/232468

snippet.textDisplay: You didn't realize Kobe had touched so many people until this.  I think this is his legacy, touching so many people not just in the US but around the world. Kobe had this charisma, smile, the will to become excellence that I think people can identify and love with.  He is like the other side of Jordan to me, a duplicate.  This brings me to Jordan.  I think Jordan if he is still playing and had his life cut short he would have the same effect all over the world.  Another person that I can think of that have this kind of effect in the world is Bruce Lee.  Michael Jackson would have the same powerful effect in the world had he past away at his prime, like 1988-1989.

snippet.textDisplay:
I was a 8 year old boy who watched his first Laker game watching Magic Johnson humiliate people with a smile on his face while wearing the beautiful purple and gold i was in awe not knowing I was witnessing one of the best franchises to ever exist blind to the fact it was only about to get better in a few years.  falling in love with a sport that I would practice and play until I could not move my legs.from practicing dribbling in my driveway driving my parents and my neighbors nuts learning how to do crossovers without lifting my legs to the basic fundamentals of just protecting the ball as if it was your most prized possession that you would never let go of. To climbing on trash cans just so we could dunk the ball like our heros .Before the age of the internet grabbing ever sports section out of my uncle's paper to see who won the  NBA games the day before .from getting in trouble for staying up way past my bedtime to watch Laker games with my big toe on the power button to turn my TV off when I heard my parents coming.to ripping off every kid in the neighborhood to trade to get the best Lakers cards. My whole life revolved around basketball and the Lakers. My mom and dad painted my room purple and gold and was decorated with  everything Lakers from bed sheets to curtains they could tell i had a passion for the sport and this franchise Always scared that I was never going to see them win a championship. Three years later my whole basketball world would change waking up on a morning in 1996 to see the front page of the sports section with the news of 17 year old kid only 6 years older then me was traded to the lakers along with Shaquille O'Neal .not knowing at the time this duo would make history and wreak havoc on the league. Not knowing exactly what to expect from a kid out of highschool that the lakers traded away few good players to acquire.kobe set on the bench his first 2 years as a laker. for 2 years i thought the franchise had made a huge mistake.1997 kobe won the dunk contest at all star weekend a small glimpse of the mamba mentality that was to come it was his first nba award and would NOT be his last.when he became a starter for the lakers is when things changed. The 1999-2000 nba season kobe won his first nba title i cried so much out of joy this was a feeling i had never felt before i didnt know how to accept that my team just won a championship little did i know i would have to get used to it atleast four more times . We did it agian the next year and agian after that i had just seen my team win a 3-peat i knew for sure that nobody could beat us with the team and the coach we had..then it happen 2002-2003 season kobe played all 82 games that year while shaq had foot surgery they lost to the spurs in the Western Conference Finals. I was distraught not knowing if this era was comming to a end already. The next year they made it to the finals only to lose to the Miami Heat this was more crushing..after that season kobe and shaqs disagreements came to light for only shaq to be traded to the Heat after losing to them that season in the finals seem to be such a slap in the face... but it would not bring kobe down only made him more of the mamba that i fell in love with he was more destin to win without shaq! Watching him give everything his body could dish out to being the most clutch player that anybody could ever be. Watching him limp at times or hold his knee on the bench i could tell this sport was taking its toll. And i knew that hes was getting older as so was i. Not wanting to think bout him leaving the game and what it would be like without him i pushed those thoughts to the side and relished in the days of greatsness. 2008-2009 was dramatic as it got with the company of a new big man pau gasol and lots of other role players in the mix along with a few nba veterans kobe would win his first title with out the man they said he could not do it with out beating the orlando magic in the finals.... the 2009- 2010 kobe would win back too back titles and the glory days were back... we are back on top agian!!!! This was beautiful in ten years i watched my team win 5 rings! Most people are lucky to get one or even make it to the playoffs ... the dominance of winning 3 in a row and then 2 in a row hadnt been done since the bulls in the 1990s......... its wasnt all bout winning rings its the fashion that kobe did it in and the things he taught me along the way... the cut throat mentality was out of this world and one that i would take on when i played for diffrent teams ..the look in his eyes and the mannerisms kobe diplayed during games did and still does give me chill bumps to this day and made me push myself when i played made me attack players physically and none the less mentally!! .made me see red when the other team had the ball and thought me my opponent was only as good as i allowed them to be and was the most exciting NBA basketball i will ever witness ....in 2013 i watched my biggest hero the guy i put on a pedestal over all other athletes go to the ground and grab the back of his ankle.. anyone who have played or watched only knew what this ment father time had peaked its ugly fucking head..i didnt wanna belive it most players are never the same after injuring their Achilles but kobe was far from most players but i knew without kobe the lakers would not get far... the reality of a kobe-less team and or league was creeping in my. head and scary...then the inevitable finnaly happen on april 13th 2016 kobe announced his retirement the end of a era had come...i was sad but happy that i witnessed 20 years of the greatest Laker of all-time... To kobe bryant thank you for showing me what deication and passion to a sport truly is. Thank you for teaching me how important it was to put everything you had into each minute of every game. Thank you for teaching me how to get into other players heads. Thank you for teaching me how to fade away and hit shots that nobody could block. Thank you for staying with the lakers for 20 years even at times u wanted to be traded. Thank You for 5 titles that i thought i would never see. Thank u for scoring 81 points in one game. Thank you for scoring 61 in your last game just remind the world who the fuck you are. Thank you Kobe Bean Bryant!!!!!!!!!!! 33/8/24 MAMBA!!!!!!!

￼
